('4c8b84a0-d1ec-11e8-bd55-3bd680a2c58a', 'Cooperating Teachers’ and Principals’ Assessment on USeP-Bislig Practicum Implementation: A basis for enhancement', '\"[{\\\"id\\\":0,\\\"name\\\":\\\"PROF. LORLY P. CAPERIDA\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\" PROF. LOURDES L. BAUYA & PROF. LOVELLA C. DE RAMOS\\\"}]\"', '<h3>Abstract</h3><br><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:107%\">Practicum program is a relevant experience necessary\r\nto enhance student teacher in the field of teaching. This is an opportunity\r\nwhere the aspiring teacher will put all theories learned into actual practice.\r\nIt will also expose the student to become familiar with the culture, the\r\nenvironment, and the roles and responsibilities of a teacher. Such chance will\r\nhelp the student teacher shape his pedagogical skills in teaching. However,\r\nduring the exposure there were tendencies where an institution cannot\r\naccomplish its tasks of providing appropriate skills and experience deemed\r\nnecessary for a student to acquire. Thus, the researchers become interested to\r\nassess how USeP-Bislig implemented the practicum program in order to evaluate\r\nweak points and come up with possible intervention for enhancement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:107%\">This study seek to answer the following objectives;\r\n(1) Determine the Cooperating Teachers’ (CTs) and Principals’ assessment of the\r\nUSeP-Bislig Practicum implementation, (2) Identify the area of program\r\nimplementation that is given the lowest score, (3) List the recommendations of\r\nthe CTs and Principals with regards to the practicum program implementation,\r\n(4) Formulate guidelines based on the CTs’ and principals’ comments and\r\nrecommendations. In order to help assess the school of its program\r\nimplementation, selected Cooperating Teachers and Principals of the Bislig City\r\nDivision are requested to evaluate through a questionnaire evaluating the\r\ndeployment process, program monitoring, student’s preparation and practicum\r\nrequirements. The items were rated on a five point Likert scale. The\r\nquestionnaires were distributed to the different schools and were retrieved 10\r\ndays.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:107%\">To determine the Cooperating Teachers and Principals’\r\nassessment on USeP-Bislig practicum implementation the descriptive method using\r\nthe survey was used. Mean was used to described the respondents’ assessment on\r\nthe four areas of practicum implementation. Result showed that (1) USeP-Bislig\r\nfollowed the practicum deployment process however there is a need to conduct\r\nthe practicum program orientation not only to the school head but to the\r\ncooperating teachers as well. (2) Practicum monitoring was always observed (3)\r\nFor the student teacher preparation, Commitment and management of learning were\r\nalways observed but practicum students lack knowledge of subject matter and\r\nteaching for independent learning. (4) USeP Bislig student teachers submitted\r\ntheir practicum requirements. (5) Of the four areas evaluated practicum\r\nrequirements rank the lowest.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:\r\n107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN-PH;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Cooperating\r\nteachers and principals recommended the following; (1) USeP-Bislig should\r\nconduct massive orientation not only to the principals’/school heads but to the\r\ncooperating teachers, (2) USeP-Bislig should continue to monitor their student\r\nteachers and have a constant communication with the Dep.Ed personnel. (3)\r\nConduct training and seminars to the student teachers to enhance the\r\ncommunication skills and their knowledge of their field.</span><br>', 'Assessment', 4, 23, 228, '2015-12-01', '2016-06-01', 'Usep- Research division/ University Funded Project', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USEP-Bislig R#7.pdf', 196604, 1, 1, '5ed3c6a0-c880-11e8-9bd6-e11af0701d8a', '2018-10-17 01:09:06', '2018-10-17 01:09:06'),
