('5797c1f0-d350-11e8-a513-8fbe7bf30fe8', 'Feasibility study on offering a four -year Bachelor of Science in Industrial Technology (BSIT) Program at the Technology Department of USeP Bislig Campus', '\"[{\\\"id\\\":0,\\\"name\\\":\\\"PROF. PHILIP B. DESPARES\\\"}]\"', '<h3>Abstract</h3><br><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"938\" style=\"width: 703.2pt; border: none;\">\r\n <tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;\r\n  height:73.15pt\">\r\n  <td width=\"127\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:95.3pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;height:73.15pt\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n  normal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"\">The\r\n  research is a feasibility study on offering a four-year bachelor of science\r\n  in industrial technology (BSIT) program at the technology department of USeP\r\n  Bislig campus. Using descriptive research and Owen’s clarificative evaluation\r\n  model, a semi structured questionnaire was developed to gather data and\r\n  analysis. Informal interviews were also carried out to gather substantial\r\n  information. The participants of the study were fourth year students from two\r\n  public secondary high schools and one private high school. Employees from two\r\n  different industries, constituents from barangay Maharlika, its faculty\r\n  members, as well as some students were considered as respondents based on the\r\n  recommendation of the research director. By means of descriptive statistics\r\n  figures were then interpreted and evaluated in coming up with the conclusion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n  normal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"\">With\r\n  the implementation of the F to 12 program USeP Bislig will continue to adapt\r\n  in this changing times. Hence, engaged in high impact research, statistics\r\n  showed the respondents eagerness when asked if there is a need to offer a\r\n  four-year Bachelor of Science in Industrial Technology (BSIT) Program.\r\n  Overwhelming, 90% of the respondents said is yes, only 2% answered no and 7%\r\n  were not sure. With this initial data and all the others incorporated in the\r\n  result of the survey, the need to need to upscale its program, that of a\r\n  3-year Diploma of Technology (DT), to add another, a 4 year of Bachelor of\r\n  Science in Industrial Technology (BSIT) program is deemed necessary.<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>', '(BSIT),offering a four -year ,echnology Department', 4, 23, 228, '2013-03-01', '2013-08-01', 'Usep- Research division/ University Funded Project', '15800.00', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Feasibility study on offering a four year degree....pdf', 543038, 1, 1, '5ed3c6a0-c880-11e8-9bd6-e11af0701d8a', '2018-10-18 19:37:45', '2018-10-18 19:37:45'),
