('c1584550-cd25-11e8-b6d6-7f46ec8b1447', 'Establishment of seed Production Area (SPA) of existing strands of Mollucan Sau (Falcata) Paraserianthesfalcataria in Usep-Bislig Camous, Bislic City: A green production within', '\"[{\\\"id\\\":0,\\\"name\\\":\\\"FOR. WHELSON C. PASOS\\\"}]\"', '<h3>Abstract</h3><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; The search for best candidate plus trees was conducted to: evaluate the phenotypic characteristic of existing strands in USEP-Bislig Campus as initial drive to conduct tree improvement program especially in establishing seed for production area (SPA) for academic use and green production as well. All existing strands of Mollucan Sau with 15 CM (DBH) are considered as candidate plus trees (CPT) Evaluated parameters include stem straightness, forking, circulatory,health,branch angle,branch thickness and branch pruning habit. Evaluation of indiuvidual strand was done using class-grade and rank method. 15 out of 84 candidate plus trees (CPT) were evaluated and accepted as plus trees. The evaluation and examination of individual candidate plus trees were done using the class-grade and ranking method. The highest mean value was observed at CPT-35 with 5.29 and followed by CPT-8 which 5.0. Thirteen strands were considered fairly acceptable or still these are strands accepted as part of the inclusion in establishing seed production area (SPA). Likewise, traits that have been examined as selected plus trees (PT) have a fair values ranging value from 3.93 as the lowest, and 4.67 as the highest value, these were both observed in stem forking and stem circularity. The lowest mean value was observed at branch thickness habit. The soil textures in seed production in study are represented by 4 texture types, namely: clay loam. Silty caly, clay loam and silty clay ranked first with 33% percent, followed by silty clay 27% and loam with 7%. Results of the analysis and its distribution of Ph value ranges from 4.5 to 7.3 where 46.7% of the PTs grows on 5.1 to 5.5 Ph-strongly acidic. About 26.7% of the PT grows on neutral soil,\r\nwhile 13.3% of grows on extremely acidic soil at and 5.6 to 6Ph. Medium acidic.&nbsp;&nbsp;Both nitrogen and potassium have sufficient\r\nlevels in all PTs and are ranged from low to high values, while phosphorus has\r\nno result, chemical do not response during the repeated trials of observations.</p>', 'Candidate Plus trees, Plus trees ,seed production area and edaphic factors', 2, 12, 122, '2008-04-01', '2010-04-01', 'Usep- Research division/ University Funded Project', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Usep-Bislig #2.pdf', 181708, 1, 1, '5ed3c6a0-c880-11e8-9bd6-e11af0701d8a', '2018-10-10 23:17:47', '2018-10-10 23:17:47'),
