('df93cd90-cd35-11e8-b597-e10b1b714dfe', 'Resource and Ecological Assessment of Bislig Bay, Philippines: Basis for Coastal Resource Management Development Intervention', '\"[{\\\"id\\\":0,\\\"name\\\":\\\"DR. FRANCO G. PANTALEON\\\"}]\"', '<h3>Abstract</h3><br><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"938\" style=\"width: 703.2pt; border: none;\">\r\n <tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;\r\n  height:73.15pt\">\r\n  <td width=\"117\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:87.95pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;height:73.15pt\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\r\n  normal\"><span lang=\"EN-PH\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt\">The\r\n  study assessed the resource and ecological condition of Bislig Bay,\r\n  Philippines in the four coastal communities of Lawigan, Labisma, Tumanan, and\r\n  Caguyao. The ecological assessment of mangroves and seagrass adopted the\r\n  descriptive method of the Participatory Coastal Resource Assessment Manual\r\n  Guide 2004. Coral reef assessment used Line Intercept Transect Method by\r\n  English et al. (1994). The physical, chemical, and microbiological water\r\n  quality were assessed with reference to Department Administrative Oder No. 34\r\n  Series of 1990. The sedimentation rates of rivers were also assessed. Results\r\n  of the study revealed that mangroves are in excellent but disturbed\r\n  condition, seagrass is in fair but highly disturbed condition, corals are in\r\n  poor and highly disturbed condition. Results of water quality parameters\r\n  revealed an indication of a high concentration of bacteria, nutrients, and\r\n  pollutants. Results revealed that the sedimentation rates of rivers are way\r\n  below the threshold value to affect the health conditions of mangrove,\r\n  seagrass, and corals. The results revealed strong evidences that the\r\n  ecological and resource condition of Bislig Bay is in a disturbed condition\r\n  that needs Coastal Resource Management Development Interventions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>', 'Assessment, percent cover, mangrove, seagrass,corals ,water quality', 2, 12, 119, '2018-01-01', '2018-12-01', 'Usep- Research division/ University Funded Project', '-2', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Usep-Bislig R#6.pdf', 180832, 1, 1, '5ed3c6a0-c880-11e8-9bd6-e11af0701d8a', '2018-10-11 01:13:10', '2018-10-11 01:13:10'),
