('f2d61a20-cd2d-11e8-901d-31a3d43a77a2', 'Assessment of Usep Bislig Program Offering', '\"[{\\\"id\\\":0,\\\"name\\\":\\\"PROF. LORLY P. CAPERIDA\\\"}]\"', '<h3>Abstract</h3><p><br></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Relevance of USEP-Bislig program offering was conducted to evaluate the relevance of the current programs offered in the camopus. Purposive, convenience and snow ball sampling were used for the selection of the respondents. This investigation was done to answer the following&nbsp;objectives: (1) To determine the preferred program to\r\nbe offered in USeP-Bislig as perceived by the (a.) High School Graduating\r\nstudents, (b.) Parents, (c.) Industry; (2) To determine the employability of\r\nUSeP-Bislig graduate; (3) To recommend policy option to the university\r\nmanagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Result\r\nof the survey revealed that (1) education, engineering, nursing, commerce and\r\nHRM are the top baccalaureate degrees preferred by high school graduating\r\nstudent’s while com.tech; nursing aide, info.tech., com. sec. and midwifery are\r\nthe preferred vocational courses and caregiver and basic driving and trouble\r\nshooting for short term courses; (2) employability for engineering graduates is\r\n77%, 79% for the forestry and 90% employability for technology graduates; (3)\r\npropose for the offering of the identified baccalaureate, vocational and short\r\nterm courses as preferred by the respondents.&nbsp;<br></p>', 'USEP-Bislig', 4, 23, 228, '2018-04-01', '2018-05-01', 'Usep- Research division/ University Funded Project', '10000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Usep-Bislig R#3.pdf', 147505, 1, 1, '5ed3c6a0-c880-11e8-9bd6-e11af0701d8a', '2018-10-11 00:16:26', '2018-10-11 00:16:26'),
